==English==
===Etymology===
From the [[w:Old English|OE]] ''[[geomor]]'', ("to [[camplain]]"), from the [[w:German language|German]] ''[[jammer]]'', ("lamentation").

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-yammer.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Intransitive Verb===
'''yammer'''
# To complain peevishly
# To talk loudly; to make an [[outcry]].
# (''[[w:Scottish English|Scottish English]]'') To lament.
# (''[[w:Scottish English|Scottish English]]'') To [[yearn]] for something.

===Synonyms===
*[[complain]]
*[[whine]]
*[[grumble]]

===Transitive Verb===
'''yammer'''
# To [[utter]] [[clamorously]]

===Synonyms===
*[[prattle]]
*[[babble]]
*[[yak]]

===Noun===
'''yammer'''
# The act or noise of yammering
# (''[[w:Scottish English|Scottish English]]'') A [[cry]] of [[lamentation]].
# (''[[w:Scottish English|Scottish English]]'') The act of '''yammer'''ing.
# (''Standard English'') A loud [[noise]].
# One who yammers.

